text:
¬†@OrionLt¬† 
I'm sorry, but you don't understand the evolutionary mechanism behind that either.
What you're talking about is historically true, but takes thousands of years of co-evolution to end up like this.
In the short term (which is decades and centuries in evolutionary terms), anything can happen.

This is pointless.
You'll see, we're not getting less dangerous variants (to those who have no prior exposure and no vaccination) anytime soon.
It's more likely we'll be getting increasingly dangerous variants as ACE2 binding affinity is important for transmissibility, which is currently still the by far most important evolutionary driver.
Unfortunately increased ACE2 binding affinity also results in a more severe disease...

The better the virus can access our cells, the less viruses are needed to infect us on average -> higher transmissibility.

The better the virus can access our cells, the faster it spreads in our body.
->
The faster it spreads, the less time our immune system has and the more damage is done before our immune system can stop the infection.

This is quite the vicious circle in this particular kind of virus that has been going on with each new major variant that has replaced other variants.

Original Wuhan strain -> Alpha mutant strain -> Delta mutant strain -> Omicron mutant strain*


*As far as we can tell Omicron has further increased ACE2 binding affinity and therefore will most definitely result in more severe disease on average in people without prior exposure and who are unvaccinated.


Edit:
Just saw your first comment.
* sigh *
No bro, you are wrong because you don't understand these things and you'll see it in the upcoming months and years.
There's no programming to become less dangerous in viruses. Things occur randomly in replication errors and the things that are beneficial pull through.
So it's all random with evolution shaping things over many generations.

Omicron will not be less dangerous on average for those without prior exposure and the unvaccinated.
Mark my words.

text:
APPEAL FOR AN ANTI-GLOBALIST ALLIANCE
By Archbishop Carlo Maria Vigan√≤
November 16, 2021	
For two years now we have been witnessing a global coup d‚Äô√©tat, in which a financial and ideological elite has succeeded in seizing control of part of national governments, public and private institutions, the media, the judiciary, politicians and religious leaders.
All of these, without distinction, have become enslaved to these new masters who ensure power, money and social affirmation to their accomplices.
Fundamental rights, which up until yesterday were presented as inviolable, have been trampled underfoot in the name of an emergency: today a health emergency, tomorrow an ecological emergency, and after that an internet emergency.
This global coup d‚Äô√©tat deprives citizens of any possibility of defense, since the legislative, executive, and judicial powers are complicit in the violation of law, justice, and the purpose for which they exist.
It is a global coup d‚Äô√©tat because this criminal attack against citizens extends to the whole world, with very rare exceptions.
It is a world war, where the enemies are all of us, even those who unwittingly have not yet understood the significance of what is happening.
It is a war fought not with weapons but with illegitimate rules, wicked economic policies, and intolerable limitations of natural rights.
Supranational organizations, financed in large measure by the conspirators of this coup d‚Äô√©tat, are interfering in the government of individual nations and in the lives, relationships, and health of billions of people.
They are doing it for money, certainly, but even more so in order to centralize power so as to establish a planetary dictatorship.
It is the Great Reset of the World Economic Forum, the Agenda 2030 of the United Nations.
It is the plan of the New World Order, in which a Universal Republic enslaves everyone and a Religion of Humanity cancels Faith in Christ.
*
In the face of this global coup d‚Äô√©tat, it is necessary to form an international Anti-Globalist Alliance, which gathers all those who want to oppose the dictatorship, who have no intention of becoming slaves to a faceless power, who are not willing to cancel their own identity, their own individuality, their own religious faith.
If the attack is global, the defense must also be global.
I call upon rulers, political and religious leaders, intellectuals and all people of good will, inviting them to unite in an Alliance that launches an anti-globalist manifesto, refuting point-by-point the errors and deviations of the dystopia of the New World Order and proposing concrete alternatives for a political program inspired by the common good, the moral principles of Christianity, traditional values, the protection of life and the natural family, the protection of business and work, the promotion of education and research, and respect for Creation.
This Anti-Globalist Alliance will have to bring together the Nations that intend to escape the infernal yoke of tyranny and affirm their own sovereignty, forming agreements of mutual collaboration with Nations and peoples who share their principles and the common yearning for freedom, justice, and goodness.
It will have to denounce the crimes of the elite, identify those responsible, denounce them to international tribunals, and limit their excessive power and harmful influence.
It will have to prevent the action of the lobbies, above all by fighting against the corruption of state officials and those who work in the information industry, and by freezing the capital used to destabilize the social order.
In Nations where governments are subservient to the elite, they will be able to establish popular resistance movements and committees of national liberation, including representatives of all sectors of society who propose a radical reform of politics, inspired by the common good and firmly opposed to the neo-malthusian project of the globalist agenda.
I invite all those who want to defend traditional Christian society to meet together in an international forum, to be held as soon as possible, in which representatives of various nations come together to present a serious, concrete, and clear proposal.
My appeal is made to political leaders and to rulers who care about the good of their citizens, leaving aside the old systems of political parties and the logic imposed by a system enslaved to power and money.
I call the Christian nations together, from east to west, inviting Heads of State and the healthy forces of institutions, the economy, labor, universities, health care and information to join a common project, disrupting the old systems and putting aside the hostilities that are desired by the enemies of humanity in the name of divide et impera.
We do not accept our adversary‚Äôs rules, because they are made precisely to prevent us from reacting and organizing an effective and incisive opposition.
I call upon Nations and their citizens to ally themselves under the Cross of Our Lord Jesus Christ, the only King and Savior, the Prince of Peace. In hoc signo vinces.
Let us found this Anti-Globalist Alliance, let us give it a simple and clear program, and let us free humanity from a totalitarian regime that brings together in itself the horrors of the worst dictatorships of all time.
If we continue to delay, if we do not understand the threat that looms over us all, if we do not react by organizing ourselves into a firm and courageous resistance, this infernal regime that is establishing itself everywhere will not be able to be stopped.
And may Almighty God assist us and protect us.
+ Carlo Maria Vigan√≤, Archbishop
Former Apostolic Nuncio to the United States of America

text: ¬†@Yvonne¬† I was a chartered scientist. It is just the way I think about probability. And there are groups that would find it very easy and desirable now that it is accessible as a WMD. I would say that getting between 30 and 50 novel mutations is about as likely as winning the lottery, getting hit by lightening twice, and discovering gold in your back garden, all in the same day. Some things can mutate quickly, but it took eons to get out of the cave - so why should all these mutation be happening right now and not more gradually over time. Other SARS viruses do not mutate this quickly. The average mode of mutations per variant is 6, with a mean average of 7.23, and very few samples having more than 15 mutations. If you do some slightly more snazzy analysis, you'll find the multivariate ++ probability incredibly remote, and the Bayesian mass entirely unlikely. It is so unlikely that you can get this many mutations that I would be very interested to see what people think in a few months time. text:
Prime Minister for Life, Sir Boris Johnson has today announced a further 'regrettable' tightening of restrictions following this latest outbreak. Parliament, and the next General Election have been suspended for an 'indefinite period' - but 'cleared' MPs 'might possibly' be recalled as early as just after Christmas 2026. 

The setting-up of road-blocks and military checkpoints, together with random checks on anyone looking 
'suspiciously unvaccinated', by members of the newly-formed Covid Protection Squad -  tasked with patrolling the streets and shopping malls, and equipped with distinctive black uniforms, jackboots, and the new ICDM ('Instant Covid Detection Meter') technology - have been announced.

The ICDM was developed following complaints that the hitherto-standard PCR system was 'only' throwing up around 90% False Positives. A collaboration between the major vaccine-manufacturers and Beijin University has produced a 'fool-proof' technology which, so its inventors say, is 'guaranteed' to produce 100% Positive results - something confirmed by 'randomised triple-blind-and-deaf' field tests on melons, calves, cow-pats, Fanta Orange, sea-water, boiling nitric acid, and Plutonium. World health supremo Dr Anthony Fauci described this developoment as "highly exciting - and exactly what we have been searching for !"

Anyone not in possession of valid 'I've been jabbed at least six times' documentation, or similar, will be
 sent to one of the new Anti-Covid Quarantine Camps currently under construction in five hundred locations throughout the UK, where they can expect to be interrogated 'rigorously', according to government sources. 

The possible use of South American cattle prods, as suggested by some extreme right-wing conspiracy 
theorists - following the reported purchase of ten thousand of them by government contractors - was described by a Home Office spokesman as "probably not very likely in most cases".

"These people will have nothing to fear, as long as they're prepared to learn the error of their ways", he said.

Additionally a new 'see-and-tell' hotline ('Scumwatch') will be set up, to enable concerned citizens to 
inform the Authorities anonymously about anyone they merely suspect may 'not be taking this crisis seriously enough', or failing to comply with the new 24 Hour Mask-Wearing Order. A ¬£2000 Good Citizen's Award, together with mortgage-relief and free fuel for car-owners for a year, will - it is hoped - 'act as a further incentive'.

"There will be no hiding place for Dissenters and Doubters", the PM said: "Whoever you are, wherever you are, we will find you - and deal with you appropriately"

Finally, he added: 

"These measures are, of course, necessary, if we are to protect the Freedom we have long cherished - and the informed, anti-social Few, will simply not be allowed to imperil the gullible, obedient Majority. The individual who thinks for himself/herself is the very LAST person we need in our New Order !"

At the end of his brief speech, even reporters applauded loudly, many of them weeping openly. The Prime Minister had to be escorted by Croatian security guards, as he pressed through the tight throng of admirers, out into the street - where placard-waving members of the newly-formed (and independent-of-government) 'Vaccine-Taking Veterans Front', accompanied by representatives of the World Vaccine-Makers Association, spontaneously chanted "Boris for King!" and "Hail to our Saviour - the Greatest Man in the History of the World, if not the Entire Cosmos!" 

Another, smaller group of so-called 'Vaccine-Takers' Lives Matter' protesters, carrying their now-familiar 'Stone All Non-Vaxxers to Death !!' placards, were ushered away from the cameras, and dispersed with the aid of cash bribes. 

(This report has been fact-checked by Tabitha Snowflake, Senior Misinformation Officer at the BBC)

text: There is a piece of laughable misinformation going around that has to be corrected, viruses DO NOT always become more mild as they get more infections. They can... or they can not. The spanish flu's second strain was more deadly than the first but soon became a mild epidemic virus (though with nasty mini pandemic stains, eg hong kong flu etc, appearing every few decades). Smallpox, AIDS and Polio as well as many, many other viruses DID NOT become less severe as they mutated. We don't know if covid will become more mild, stay the same or become more severe. So for those peddling that myth - stop lying!

text:
For all those asking why the reported "mild" symptoms warrant a "variant of concern" and pose a "high risk", it's because the cases so far have been largely in a young healthy and immune-protected population who are the first to spread diseases like this and least likely to suffer severe consequences. The concern comes from a few things - the likely affect of it when it reaches the more vulnerable and unvaccinated populations around the world, and also because the virus has had a significant amount of vital mutations that theoretically help it spread easier and evade some immune protection, and to reflect that, the incident rate of this variant in South Africa has increases rapidly which indicates these hypotheses might have some backing. On top of that, the fact we don't know much about this variant yet is a reason to take precautions.
If you actually watch this video, the infection disease doctor from South Africa says as much - the cases are rising rapidly in a fairly well immunised population and so are the hospitalisation rates among the unvaccinated. He even explains that despite "anecdotal" reports of mild symptoms, we should be cautious because it's too early to understand all the factors at play. The only things he opposes are the border restrictions because he thinks they're ineffective and that the variant will sweep the world regardless.

The doctor who discovered Omicron says symptoms from the variant are ‚Äúextremely mild‚Äù and has accused the UK of ‚Äúpanicking unnecessarily‚Äù.


The UK government announced the reintroduction of masks in shops and on public transport and imposed new travel restrictions after two cases of Omicron were detected in Britain.

Omicron, first detected in Botswana, has sparked alarm among scientists over fears that it could be more contagious than other variants and resistant to vaccines.

But Dr Angelique Coetzee, chair of the South African Medical Association, said the UK is overreacting, adding that symptoms are ‚Äúextremely mild‚Äù.

She told the Andrew Marr Show that she first discovered the variant in a man in his early 30s who displayed symptoms of tiredness and a mild headache.

text:
¬†@6502-Coder¬† That is correct but it doesn't mean that it's use doesn't work. Tooth floss is used in hygeine but I quite happily use it to cut cheese in my house! 

Kary Mullis said ‚ÄúPCR is intended to identify substances qualitatively, but by its very nature is unsuited for estimating numbers. Although there is a common misimpression that the viral load tests actually count the number of viruses in the blood, these tests cannot detect free, infectious viruses at all; they can only detect proteins that are believed, in some cases wrongly, to be unique to HIV. The tests can detect genetic sequences of viruses, but not viruses themselves.‚Äù Unfortunately he died in 2019 so is unable to discuss his work further. However this does not mean that the test does not work. He is clarifying that PCR identifies substances qualitatively not quantitatively, detecting the genetic sequences of viruses, but not the viruses themselves, and thus it can show that the person has the viral proteins but cannot determine viral load. i.e. the person has been infected but may or may not be infectious.

author: Joseph Weeks

text:
@Joseph Weeks  Yes, as people in this group say, our betters are very entertaining. The Berliners call them Bonzen, and have a long tradition of being irreverent to them.
What I love about Brittish tradition is the unashamed admission of this by educated men becomming decidedly eccentric ...
In terms of the models. A model really is there to serve a purpose.Yes, models of the nature you describe would be used to monitor the evolution of the disease. We had about six different models in my country, and each was built for a different purpose. Of these models the ones I found most interesting were the models as to the financial implications of a Lockdown. I preferred models based on Markov chains, mostly because they allowed me to understand what was going on. When I realised there was not going to be any meaningful public discussion, I lost interest. You really want to be using your non-linear dynamics when you have moved from understanding (different from monitoring) to control. A nonlinear system, once you have an accurate description of reality, can in the end be controlled much more effectively and efficienctly. So you want to move from a strategy of something like flatten the curve and then keep the health system at a comfortable level, which we may have already achieved. The next month or so will tell.
In terms of the pandemic being real, I don't think that is in dispute, but there is also little doubt that our response to the pandemic is causing serious hardship. And people will be affected differently. I think what the Nanny state is doing badly is that it is run by left brain people, who have no comprehension of the people who are articulating their hardships. I think when you listen to right brained people, or people that think differently to you, you have to listen differently. You listen for the ardent prayer of the Mother for the Son. With other words you listen to the dreams they have for their descendants, and then only do you listen to what they say. It gives you the right context and frame.
In terms of Covid colonialism (I think Covid apartheid is too narrow a term, and too much in the paradigm and language of big pharma), I would point out that Covid affects people differently. Rich people it is predominantly about the lives of their elderly and loved ones, poor people it is predominantly about livelyhood (we have grafiti around saying "Money, not masks"). What I find so satisfying is that our scientists are beginning to snap out of this and beginning to see things in a more balanced fashion. That is why we are so critical of the UK, USA and Europe shutting their borders with Omicron. We have a petition signed by about twenty of our top epedimologists asking the government not to do another lockdown, liquer and travel ban. We are becoming more compassionate to and protective of our weakest members in society, and that can only bode well for all of us. We are hoping that the Covid colonisers will follow.
In terms of interspecies transmission (natural or otherwise), it is a real cause for concern. There are about fifty potential candidates in Asia, a similar number in Africa and a few less in South America. The way I understand it is that the initial work on making a vaccine is not so bad, it is the part that needs safety testing that is so expensive. So it probably means that we need to expand the type of work done in places like Wuhan considerably, in order to mitigate the risk. What plays against that is that wild places are disappearing. What really shocked me, was that 70% of animal biomass is used by humans. So most species are going to be gone before we encounter them. My feeling is that we will probably have one or two more interspecies epeidemics before the window closes.
author: Martin Muller

author: Joseph Weeks

text:
‚Äã @Joseph Weeks  Look, no worries. Mostly curious and  looking for common ground, something you know that I don't and something interesting to explore. I did not realise how much of your ego is invested in your opinion. Pity.
Look March/April/May 2020 was a lovely time. Everybody was exploring to see how they could help. So exploring how to build ventilators, making models to understand the pandemic. The gentleman that built the model for monitoring the spread of the virus this side is a particle Physicist. Good Energy.  
Then it turned really dark. Lock the poor people up, send the army in to keep them in their  suburbs, This is all real. I look after my mother's property in a village in the orange free state. The pleas for help to me as people's livelyhoods fell away. The fear in a gentleman's eyes that had worked odd jobs for me for a long time. 
Does this colour my perception of what is going on -of course it does. Is my perception biased because of this - unashamedly. I would have to have a heart of stone if it did not. Does that make my opinion baseless - I don't think so. That is more your arrogance.
My PhD is in theoretical physics. Using nonlinear dynamics (secular perturbation theory) to understand how the quantum spectrum and the clasical periodic orbits are related. So work closely related to Poincare's work around the 1890s and Bohr's work around the 1920s. So yeah, nonlinear dynamics was my old stomping ground. It was very cool to see what the greats were on about. An of course once you understand you can control.
Yes, I did pitched the conversation at a level I thought you would enjoy. Got it wrong, sorry.
author: Martin Muller

text: ¬†@Martin Muller¬† Ok, based on the detail,  it seems you are being genuine.  I likely judged you wrongly,  based on what you have written I realize that I was being overly confrontational and a bit of an ass.  I appreciate the perspective you have shared on it and will keep it in mind moving forward.  Thank you for you're incites and additions to the field of complex dynamic systems (if you made any).  I am simply newer to this then you are and this year has been , weird, knowing this much.
author: Joseph Weeks

text:
¬†@Joseph Weeks¬† The intention really was to take the conversation forward, and in whatever direction you want to take it. I was merely engaging in a way that I respond to each of your points and then allow you to agree/disagree or deepen the conversation as you see fit. I normally learn a lot if the conversation moves forward. 
For example it is very clear that you know a lot of the dtails of fine-tuning your model that I do not. And I have many questions for you, if you felt like it.
As you so correctly point out, I am not your better. We can merely share the road a bit, and it should be fun for both of us. I am decidedly Kantian in my ethical outlook. So it is to act in such a way, that if my principles were universal, that would create a society that I would like to live in.
I agree, it is deeply frustrating that it is so hard to convince people of the facts. I actually admire you that you take the responsibility of your knowledge seriously and try to do some good by moving people forward. Leading by example always helps. Educating always helps. At least they have heard the facts. It is quite amazing how powerful the truth is, if you let it work.

Once people have entrenced positions, these conversations become much more difficult. There are many conspiracy theorists in my surroundings. The worst is my wife's best friend that now lives in Greece. Her family's only real asset it an olive farm that has been in the family for generations. This pandemic has all the makings of rendering that worthless. So yes, the threat to her family's hopes and dreams are very real. She just ariculates it badly. That is really what I mean, when I say focus on the dreams the women/mother has for the Son/future. If you are able to start the conversation there, you will actually have a conversation that can change things for the better.

text:
¬†@Charlotte¬† There isn't a law of declining virulence.  There is a theory that most viruses become less pathogenic over time following a pandemic.  The theory is pretty sound but not necessarily true.  The most important factor is resilience in a surviving population and not exclusively the virus itself, although it could be.  It isn't a law because a number of viruses could be listed which disprove the rule.  
Eventually SARS-COV-2 will become less pathogenic to the remaining population but it will probably take a couple more waves from new mutations.  It's very possible that a more virulent mutation emerges before we're set for endemic equilibrium.  It may not be Omicron and  it's possible that it may not be another.  Probability suggests there may be a more virulent mutation before the pandemic is over.
